from the sea border (top of 
<figureCitation box="[1045,1132,1124,1148]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1085,1108]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,193,1064]" captionTargetId="figure-414@10.[226,1360,193,1064]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. (A) Eligmodontia dunaris MNHN 1547, paratype (Photo A. Spotorno). (B) Habitat at Playa Los Choros dunes, type locality (Photo C. Zuleta); intensive trapping at the plain belt (top, below sea border) failed to capture any Eligmodontia. (C) Eligmodontia dunaris captured and released alive at Caldera, Atacama, showing bipedal posture (Photo E. Valenzuela by permission)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5981094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5981094/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="388">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
